Marilyn Zuniga, a teacher at Forest Street School in Orange, New Jersey, has been suspended without pay pending an investigation .
She sent her third-grade class to write letters to Mumia Abu-Jamal in prison following his hospitalization last month .
The letters were delivered to him as he was recovering in hospital from complications from diabetes .
A second batch of students, from the Philadelphia Student Union, also sent the letters .
Zuniga will remain suspended until the investigation is complete .